      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_abqQ6z": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "I already eat somewhat healthily. Why do I need this?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Most Indian home meals like rice, dal, roti, sabzi are strong on carbohydrates and light on complete protein, B-vitamins, and specific minerals like magnesium and iodine. The National Nutrition Monitoring Bureau consistently flags these gaps in urban Indian diets.<br/><br/>More Green SMP is not a replacement for a healthy diet. It is one spoonful added to the food you already cook, closing nutritional gaps without adding a new habit. If your protein, B-vitamin, potassium, and magnesium intake are already optimal every day then you probably do not need it. For most people, they are not.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_wRYLDi": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is this safe for daily use? What about children and pregnant women?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>More Green SFMGP contains one ingredient: sunflower microgreen powder. No additives, preservatives, or synthetic compounds.<br/><br/>For healthy adults: safe for daily use at 5-10g per day.<br/>For children (3+): safe in smaller amounts (2-3g) mixed into food.<br/>For pregnant or breastfeeding women: sunflower microgreen is a whole food. That said, always consult your doctor before adding any supplement during pregnancy.<br/>For people on blood-thinning medication: the product contains Vitamin K. Speak to your physician if you are on anticoagulants.<br/><br/>FSSAI Licensed. NABL tested. No synthetic inputs.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_FbCGgM": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How do I know the product is what it says it is?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>The supplement market in India has a trust problem with unverified claims, unlicensed products, labels that do not reflect what is in the pouch.<br/><br/>More Green was built to be the opposite:<br/>→ FSSAI Licensed (No. 21225195001665) - regulated as a food product from Day 1<br/>→ Single ingredient: Sunflower Microgreen Powder. The label is the truth.<br/>→ NABL-accredited independent lab testing at Equinox Labs, Navi Mumbai<br/>→ Full lab reports available on request: founders@moregreen.in<br/>→ Grown in our own polyhouse in Bengaluru. Not outsourced, not opaque<br/><br/>We are a small brand with our names on every pouch. We have every incentive to be accurate and no incentive not to be.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_tnDMk3": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "There are other green powders. Why this one?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Three reasons.<br/><br/>1. Category: SMP is not spirulina, moringa, or wheatgrass. Sunflower microgreen powder is a different ingredient with a different nutritional profile. Notably 51.85g of protein, which no other green powder in this category matches.<br/><br/>2. Whole food vs extract: Most competitors use heat-processed extracts. More Green is naturally dehydrated whole microgreen. The co-factor nutrition survives.<br/><br/>3. Verified: NABL-accredited independent lab testing on the actual product. Not a database value. Not a supplier claim. The specific batch you are buying, tested.<br/><br/>One more: there is no other commercially available Sunflower Microgreen Powder in India. You are not choosing between competitors. You are choosing whether to try a new category.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_KXbR9Q": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How soon will I feel results?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Many people start noticing improvements in energy and overall well-being within a few days to a couple of weeks. Consistency is key to getting the best results. This is \"An apple a day...\" case.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
